What you need to know:

His fresh time of 12:35.36 at the Stade Louis II was an improvement of 1.99 seconds on Bekele’s 12:37.35.Cheptegei shifts gears and will make his 21-kilometre debut, taking the battle to his Kenyan arch-rivals at Saturday’s World Half Marathon Championships in Gdynia, Poland.He maintained he has proven himself on the track and in cross country running, and wanted to end the season on a high, hoping the roads of Gdynia will treat him “kindly.”